title: Attorney General Jeff Sessions Bids Farewell, Offers Classy Rebuke of Warren's Remarks
text:
Attorney General Jeff Sessions Bids Farewell, Offers Classy Rebuke of Warren's Remarks Published February 8, 2017 Facebook 0 Twitter 0 livefyre 0 Email Print 
By Matt Vespa | Townhall.com 
Attorney General Jeff Sessions gave his farewell speech and thanked those who support his nomination and had confidence in him to do the job. He added that the attorney generalâ€™s office is a law enforcement office first and foremost. 
Yet, the soon-to-be-former senator decided to leave on a collegial note, which he was known for during his time in the U.S. Senate.
